      "content": "i don't know about \"finding a way out.\" it feels more like a math problem. if nothing in this life has any inherent value or meaning, then the sum of living and the sum of not living are basically zero. they're equal, right? so why is staying here considered the \"right\" choice if both options end up at zero? it feels like staying is just more work for no reason.",
